snippet: As Iraqis on Saturday celebrated Id al-Fitr, the holiday that marks the end of Ramadan, a string of car bombs struck in mostly Shiite neighborhoods, killing more than 60 people, officials said.
abstract: String of car bombs explodes in mostly Shiite neighborhoods across Iraq, killing at least 61 people and wounding more than 200.

byline.contributor: Michael R. Gordon contributed reporting from Washington, and Yasir Ghazi from Baghdad.

lead_paragraph: As Iraqis on Saturday celebrated Id al-Fitr, the holiday that marks the end of Ramadan, a string of car bombs struck in mostly Shiite neighborhoods, killing more than 60 people, officials said.

headline.main: Car Bombings Kill Scores Across Iraq
headline.print_headline: Car Bombings Kill Scores Across Iraq
